<item>
            <title>[LU-1402] cfs_alloc_flags_to_gfp should translate CFS_ALLOC_HIGH to __GFP_HIGHMEM instead of __GFP_HIGH</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1402</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;According to the comment above CFS_ALLOC_HIGH, the flag allows allocator to return memory in the highmen zone:&lt;br/&gt;
/* allow to return page beyond KVM. It has to be mapped into KVM by&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;cfs_page_map(); */&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;But cfs_alloc_flags_to_gfp() converts it to __GFP_HIGH, which according to kernel header:&lt;br/&gt;
#define __GFP_HIGH      0x20    /* Should access emergency pools? */&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think __GFP_HIGHMEM should be used instead. Also it makes sense to rename CFS_ALLOC_HIGH to CFS_ALLOC_HIGHMEM to avoid further confusion.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="14421">LU-1402</key>
            <summary>cfs_alloc_flags_to_gfp should translate CFS_ALLOC_HIGH to __GFP_HIGHMEM instead of __GFP_HIGH</summary>
