                            <comment id="38790" author="liang" created="Mon, 14 May 2012 21:14:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Isaac, there is a patch which can totally clean up our allocators: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,2523&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,2523&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
it will be landed to 2.3 after review and test&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;we probably don&apos;t need a separate patch to reduce code conflict? I guess it&apos;s not a critical bug because __GFP_HIGHMEM don&apos;t have too many use cases in Lustre and most are in obdecho,&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
